.TH "_kvm_vz_restore_htimer" 9 "_kvm_vz_restore_htimer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_kvm_vz_restore_htimer \- Restore hard timer state.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _kvm_vz_restore_htimer
.BI "(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ","
.BI "u32 compare "  ","
.BI "u32 cause "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vcpu" 12
Virtual CPU.
.IP "compare" 12
CP0_Compare register value, restored by caller.
.IP "cause" 12
CP0_Cause register to restore.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Restore hard timer Guest.Count & Guest.Cause taking care to preserve the
value of Guest.CP0_Cause.TI while restoring Guest.CP0_Cause.
